Reasoning: The paper deals with parallel computing and algorithms for assigning unique integer names to processors in a PRAM system with shared memory. This falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses lower bounds on time and uses random bits, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the algorithms developed in the paper involve concurrent writing to shared memory cells, which is a topic in concurrency theory (cs.CC).
